    "Moreover, although CNER and CWS have common characteristics, they have differences that prevent them from completely sharing the underlying model architecture, that is, the embedding and encoding layers.",
    "Therefore, we evaluate the proposed multitask learning framework with CWS to verify its effectiveness for the CNER task.",
    "We then conduct experiments with various sharing strategies for the embedding and encoding layers between CNER and CWS to explore their effects on entity recognition.To evaluate the proposed multitask learning framework with CWS for the CNER task, BiLSTM, BiGRU, IDCNN, and BCNN are used as encoding layers in the framework to form the joint CNER models BiLSTM-CWS, BiGRU-CWS, IDCNN-CWS, and BCNN-CWS.",
